%3A1999.01.0173%3Atext%3DPhaedrus%3Asection%3D270a Perseus program] [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0174%3Atext%3DPhaedrus%3Asection%3D270a (translation)] from {{cite book\n  | last = Plato\n  | others = John Burnet (ed.)\n  | title = Platonis Opera\n  | publisher = Oxford University Press\n  | year = 1903\n  }}\n* Plutarch, ''Cimon''. See original text in [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A2008.01.0069%3Achapter%3D17%3Asection%3D6 Perseus program] [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A2008.01.0017%3Achapter%3D17%3Asection%3D6 (translation)]\n* {{cite wikisource |author=[[Plutarch]] |wslink=Lives (Dryden translation) |plaintitle=Lives |chapter=Pericles |translator=[[John Dryden]]}}. See original text in [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3atext%3a2008.01.0072 Perseus program]\n* Quintilian, ''Institutiones''. See original text in [http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/quintilian.html The Latin Library].\n* {{cite wikisource |title=History of the Peloponnesian War |author=[[Thucydides]] |translator=[[Richard Crawley]]}}, I\u2013III. See original text in [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0199%3Abook%3D1%3Achapter%3D1%3Asection%3D1 Perseus program]\n* [[Xenophon]] (?), ''[[Constitution of the Athenians (Pseudo-Xenophon)|Constitution of Athens]]''. See original text in [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0157%3Achapter%3D2%3Asection%3D16 Perseus program] [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0158%3Achapter%3D2%3Asection%3D16 (translation)]\n{{refend}}\n\n=== Secondary sources ===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book | last=Aird | first=Hamish | title=Pericles: The Rise and Fall of Athenian Democracy | publisher=The Rosen Publishing Group | year=2004 | isbn=978-0-8239-3828-5 | url=https://archive.org/details/periclesrisef00aird }}\n* {{cite journal|last=Badian|first=E.