ry: From Thucydides to the Nuclear Age|last=Ober|first=Josiah|publisher=Westview Pr |year=1991|isbn=978-0-8133-7744-5|chapter=National Ideology and Strategic Defence of the Population, from Athens to Star Wars}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ober|first=Josiah|title=The Athenian Revolution|publisher=Princeton University Press|location=Princeton, New Jersey|year=1996|isbn=978-0-691-01095-3}}\n* Paparrigopoulos, Konstantinos (Karolidis, Pavlos) (1925), ''History of the Hellenic Nation (Volume Ab)''. Eleftheroudakis (in Greek).\n* {{cite book | first=Koliopoulos Constantinos | last=Platias Athanasios G. | title=Thucydides on Strategy | publisher=Eurasia Publications| year=2006 | isbn=978-960-8187-16-0}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|title=Pericles|encyclopedia=Oxford Classical Dictionary edited by Simon Hornblower and Antony Spawforth|year=1996}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia|title=Pericles|encyclopedia=Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|year=2002}}\n* {{cite book | first= A.J. | last=Podlecki | title=Perikles and His Circle | publisher=Routledge (UK)| year=1997 | isbn=978-0-415-06794-2}}\n* {{cite book | first=Edward J. | last=Power | title=A Legacy of Learning | publisher=SUNY Press | year=1991 | isbn=978-0-7914-0610-6}}\n* {{cite book | first=P.J. | last=Rhodes | title=A History of the Classical Greek World | publisher=Blackwell Publishing | year=2005 | isbn=978-0-631-22564-5}}\n* {{cite book | first=Sarah | last=Ruden | title=Lysistrata | publisher=Hackett Publishing | year=2003 | isbn=978-0-87220-603-8}}\n* {{cite book|title=What's Wrong with Democracy?|last=Samons|first=Loren J.|publisher=University of California Press|year=2004|isbn=978-0-520-23660-8|location=Los Angeles, California|chapter=The Peloponnesian War|url=https://archive.org/details/whatswrongwithde00samo}}\n* {{cite book|title=A History of the Greek City States, 700\u2013338 B.C.|last=Sealey|first=Raphael|publisher=University of California Press|year=1976|isbn=978-0-520-03177-7|chapter=The Peloponnesian War|url=https://archive.org